Hi Everyone!

I‚Äôve just launched a new casting platform called Castingly! As I work on building a database of actors, I would like to invite you‚Äîwhether you‚Äôre an actor or simply curious‚Äîto create your profile and explore what we have to offer.

‚Ä¢ Free to Use: Enjoy all features without any cost!

‚Ä¢ Public Profile Page: Showcase your Reels/Demos/Accomplishments and share your profile with ease.

‚Ä¢ Upcoming Casting Breakdowns: Stay tuned!

‚Ä¢ Built-in Actors Forum: Connect, network, and chat with fellow actors.

Check it out at www.castingly.com

I appreciate your support! Feel free to DM me with thoughts and feedback.

**CASTING & PARTICIPATION CALL ‚Äì MADE FIGHT LEAGUE‚Ñ¢ REALITY SERIES (LAS VEGAS)**

Made Fight League‚Ñ¢ is officially recruiting for an upcoming **6-week unscripted reality series** filming in **Las Vegas** in **early 2026** (exact dates TBA).

We are hiring **both UNION and NON-UNION** talent.

This project blends **entertainment, comedy, drama, lifestyle, and competition** inside a **safe, professionally run environment**. It will be **streamed 24/7**, capturing real personalities, real moments, and real opportunity.
WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Actors (union & non-union)
‚Ä¢ Everyday people with strong personalities
‚Ä¢ Athletes & fighters
‚Ä¢ Musicians & artists
‚Ä¢ Comedians & entertainers
‚Ä¢ Creators, performers, and big characters
‚Ä¢ Anyone who believes their **experience, resources, or credit** could meaningfully support production is also encouraged to reach out
KEY DETAILS:

‚Ä¢ **Location:** Las Vegas
‚Ä¢ **Duration:** 6 weeks
‚Ä¢ **Ages:** 21‚Äì45 (must be 21+)
‚Ä¢ **Status:** Paid, role-based participation
‚Ä¢ **Travel & lodging:** Provided
‚Ä¢ **Daily per diem:** Provided
‚Ä¢ **Environment:** Safe, professional, fully managed
‚Ä¢ **Format:** Unscripted reality (entertainment, comedy, drama)
‚Ä¢ **Exposure:** Major visibility through Made Fight League‚Ñ¢ platforms

This is a **career-level opportunity**, not a hobby project. The right participants will gain exposure, content, connections, and real momentum.
HOW TO APPLY:

Email **madefightleague@gmail.com**
**Deadline:** **January 10th**

Please include:
‚Ä¢ A short description of who you are
‚Ä¢ Why you‚Äôd be a strong fit
‚Ä¢ Photos **or** social media links (Instagram preferred)

If you‚Äôve ever wanted to be part of something **bigger than a one-off gig**, this is it.

Serious inquiries only.

‚Äî **Ashlee Gambino**
Co-Founder, Made Fight League‚Ñ¢

items.text:
Call for dancers! 

Free Flow Dance Theatre‚Äôs 31st season in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, Canada

Deadline ‚Äì January 10th, 2026.

Various Paid contracts for our 2026 season.

Time Frame: March 2026 ‚Äì Nov 30, 2026

Seeking Canadian-based professional contemporary dancers of any gender aged 19+ for various paid contracts.

To view the full call head to freeflowdance.com/work-with-us or click the link in our bio.

Hired dance artists will receive free access to our Body Worker Program (monthly ‚Äì massage, fascial stretch, physio etc), free access to all Brain-Body Connection professional development workshops, regular company classes, and free monthly studio space. Several of our programs allow for the presentation of your own work. The season will also include some Festival performances. New works will be developed by resident choreographer, Jackie Latendresse and other established Canadian Artists. 

Please submit LOI, current CV, references and dance reel to ad@freeflowdance.com

#freeflowdancetheatre #yxedance #dancejobscanada #dancejobs #contemporarydance

Photo by Ken Greenhorn featuring Meghann Michalsky

items.text:
Hi everyone, I wanted to share this short film I made on a $100 budget. I am a student filmmaker, puppeteer, and musician from Rhode Island and combined all three of those to achieve this 10 min short film!

Please support this film and my filmmaking journey by watching, liking, and commenting. 

My production instagram is: @celico.film.productions if anyone is interested in collaborating and/or following my future and past work! 

https://youtu.be/knvGepPtQwg?si=4QJOAit4nCbJFd12 

Shot using a BlackMagic 4K Pocket Cinema Camera

Edited using Adobe Premiere Pro

Music Composed and Recorded on Logic Pro X and MuseScore Studio 

Puppets built by Alex Celico (me)

Puppeteered by Alex Celico, Gavin Lapan-Carpenter, Darius Caceres, Jeffrey Lopriore

Narrated by Christian Sullivan
items.previewTitle: The Story of Bliss and Blythe - 2025 [FULL MUSICAL SHORT FILM]
items.previewDescription: On Christmas Eve, two elfin toys spring to life with cheer,They roam the house as best friends do, in magic, once a year.A spark of hurt divides their hearts...

items.text:
This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

items.summary:
This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

**HORT FILM CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDIGENOUS FEMALE ACTOR**

**Project Type:** Independent Short Film
**Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Dates:** March, 2026
**ROLE**
* **Indigenous / First Nations / M√©tis / Inuit female actor**
* **Age range:** approx. 18‚Äì25
* Acting experience preferred but not required
**CHARACTER**
* A quiet, observant young woman navigating a moment of personal change.
**REQUIREMENTS**
* Must self-identify as Indigenous
* Based in Vancouver or able to work locally
* Comfortable working on an independent short film set
**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)
* (Optional) Demo reel or self-tape

**Submit to:** hiayj23@gmail.com

items.text:
''They got me an apartment in New York!''

She was close to tears on our zoom call.

''And the flight's paid for too! I even get a per diem of $100 a day! 
That's on top of what they pay me and it's A LOT, KC!''

After she got over the thrill of booking a recurring role on a series (in NY!!!) her mind was blown about everything else that came with it. 

She'd put almost 5 years of constant study with me to get to this level and she took absolutely none of it for granted. 

It was a lot of work and the work didn't stop when she got to NY. 

18 hour days.
Incredibly challenging scenes (I wish I could tell you because it's mind-blowing what she did but I can't).
Living in a country where she knew no one.

An since that series she's continued to work hard and book. 

It doesn't get easier when you find success. The challenges are different. 

You can start now and put in the work and build the muscles that help you meet those challenges. 

Or you can look back in 5 years from now and think I wish I did it. 

Regret is an ugly thing to live with. 

I have a few, but as the song goes, too few to mention. 

Donna-Marie Manning and I are very selective about who we work with. 

Your success is our success. 

We don't have these stories to tell if you don't book. So we only want to work with committed and dedicated actors.

When you fill out this form tell us everything. 

https://form.jotform.com/253125203574248

We promise we won't laugh at you or judge you for wanting to act. 

We know people sometimes do. We don't. 

Our job is helping actors make their dreams come true. 

Don't hold back. We need to know you to coach you. 

xo KC

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Sophie is also working alongside Dan Hubbard Casting, on projects such as the TV series ‚ÄòThe Gentleman‚Äô (directed by Guy Ritchie) and ‚ÄòThe Rage‚Äô (directed by Paul Greengrass).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com 

Here are the links to our free platform for Actors. Never pay or struggle for a read in for your auditions again! Join us if not on the platform already!

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

Hey everyone! Dan Bell Casting is seeking children ages **13‚Äì17** or adults **60+** to participate in a paid face-capture research study with a major social media platform.

The goal is to improve their facial filters. It pays **$350** for approximately **2.5 hours** of participation in **Los Angeles**.

If interested, please sign up using the form below:
[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc_IIH7UC8Wl8QtqqpDkonbDSU24SHMFnQqKFL5CoE3ay7jJA/viewform)

(Please keep in mind that this does involve the use of **AI facial scanning**, so please do not sign up if you are not comfortable with that.)

I've participated in the study myself and was able to complete it in an hour! Feel free to check out our Instagram @danbellcasting or call the office if you have any questions.

The goal is to improve their facial filters. It pays **$350** for approximately **2.5 hours** of participation in **Los Angeles**.

If interested, please sign up using the form below:

CASTING CALL - Vancouver, BC 

Zariya, a 20 something from a small town. She embodies the duality of light and dark femininity, delicate yet strong. She has long dark hair and darker features. She is represented by the Sun card in Tarot. She is the light within the dark, a beacon of hope. 

Title: The Burden of Transformation

Writer/Director: Salom√© Mu√±oz 

Genre: Drama

Themes: Psychological, Dreamy, Comedy within a Tragedy

Shooting dates: January 20/21 2026

You receive: copy, credit and meal! 

This project is very theatrical and over the top, a background in theatre performance/stage acting is ideal but not required. 

If you are interested, please send me headshots and a resume via [s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com](mailto:s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com) and for more information look to @theburdenoftransformation on instagram! 

Thank you!

items.text:
## **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTETRACHROMACY‚Äù (Short Film)**

**Project Title:** *Tetrachromacy*

**Genre:** Drama

**Location:** Vancouver, BC

**Shoot Dates:** December 29 & 30, 2025

**Compensation:** Indie film, great experience, Volunteer project (we are all volunteers, there‚Äôs no budget.)

Synopsis

*Tetrachromacy* follows **Nathan**, a photojournalist who loses his ability to see color after a head injury, leaving his world in stark black and white. One year later, he discovers that color returns only through AI-recreated images of his photographs. His life shifts when he encounters **Claire**, a woman in a yellow dress who appears vividly in color within his monochromatic reality, challenging his isolation and reshaping his sense of connection.

Role breakdown
NATHAN(Lead, 30s, male)

* A passionate photojournalist with a strong artistic eye
* Suffers from cerebral achromatopsia following a head injury
* Intelligent, introspective, emotionally reserved
* Slightly awkward when expressing feelings
* **Emotional arc:** moves from isolation and frustration toward wonder, openness, and human connection

**Notes:**

This is a subtle, performance-driven role. Actor must be comfortable conveying emotion through restraint, stillness, and internal conflict.

Submission Details

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (or relevant acting experience)
* Demo reel (if available)
* A short Self-tape

**Submit to:** [s6films.co@gmail.com](mailto:s6films.co@gmail.com)

**Submission Deadline:** December 21, 2025

If selected auditions will be hosted on December 22, 2025

Who we are:

S6 films is a a group of passionate filmmakers pursuing creating films we care about amidst busy life and jobs in video production.

To all our talents, producers, casters and partners ‚Äî thank you for an unforgettable 2025. We‚Äôre sharing this beautiful new film with S√∏strene Grene as a little holiday gift and a huge thank you for the trust, teamwork and artistry this year. üí´

As Choreographer/Caster ‚Äî Maria Christina Jarltoft, it felt like the best kind of time warp: the craft of commercials from 25 years ago ‚Äî and a heartbeat back on stage from my ballet years.

Full credits & thanks to:

Rasmus Skj√∏tt, Ren√© Tingskov, Lotte Korntved, Jacob Holst Mouritzen, Dennis Lee

Die Essenz-Methode. 

 

In 15 Jahren Schauspielbranche, 10 Jahren nach Gr√ºndung einer Castingagentur, und der Arbeit mit hunderten (Quer)einsteigern, wei√ü ich endlich worauf es WIRKLICH ankommt.

Ist es f√ºr dich auch Zeit? Dich wahrhaftig zu zeigen, unverwechselbar zu sein, deine Seele und deine Essenz ins Schauspiel einzubringen?

items.text:
Hi everyone!

My theatre group Thalia‚Äôs Tantrums Theatre Company has an online series that we do each year. This is our third year and we‚Äôre starting 2026 off with an actor based series ‚ÄòThe Midweek Monologue Series‚Äô in January. As this is an online series the time would be 7pm PT. However we are going to hold a showcase performance (held in Vancouver,BC) and I thought that if people wanted to showcase a monologue they always wanted to do, it could be screened alongside the live (Vancouver based) performances. 

This is a non paid project for us all, just to work on monologues and hopefully network etc. so if you wanted to take part we would screen your monologue (and provide any socials/ website info) and get you some follows/ showcase your talents.

For more info, please email thaliastantrumstheatreco@gmail.com

Or check out our website/ socials for the main notice (this is however geared for people who would be in the online session).

FREE HEADSHOT with any of my packages - my Christmas gift to you.

Book a session by Christmas (for a headshot session in the New Year) and I‚Äôll include one extra headshot completely free.

I guide you throughout the shoot to help you feel comfortable and to create a strong range of headshots that help you stand out and get noticed by casting professionals.

My studio is fully portable, so I can travel to you if you‚Äôd prefer the ease of shooting at home, or you‚Äôre welcome to come to my studio in Grantham, Lincolnshire.

or feel free to message me directly here on FB.

We‚Äôre looking for fabulous new faces to join A Roman Rumble ‚Äì The Rude Panto, touring across Yorkshire, Nottinghamshire and beyond from November 2026 to January 2027.

We‚Äôre casting:

  2 x Roman Guards ‚Äì male chorus, ideal for newcomers

 ‚Ä¢ 3 x Female Chorus ‚Äì market traders, handmaidens etc.

2 x lead male roles - villainous sidekick & silly boy

We welcome all backgrounds, body types & experience levels. Must be up for a laugh, willing to sing & dance (badly is fine!) and give it your all.

This is unpaid, volunteer work ‚Äì just like the rest of us. We do it for the love of it, not the money. All income goes back into making the show more brilliant and bonkers each year.

We‚Äôve been proudly described as ‚Äúabhorrent satire masquerading as pantomime.‚Äù

We call it mega fabby ace brill.

Faroutrachael@gmail.com

items.text:
The Cottage
By Sandy Rustin
Directed by Ben Green
Auditions:
Monday, January 5, and Tuesday, January 6 at @ 7:00pm
Callback by invitation on Wednesday January 7 @ 7pm

Play Overview:
A fast-paced, heightened comedic farce set in 1923 England. Infidelity, mistaken identities, exaggerated manners, and bold physical comedy drive the show. All roles require strong comedic timing, physicality, and the ability to deliver heightened, crisp dialogue in a British dialect.

The director encourages diverse casting. No role has a strict requirement of ethnicity or race.

Physicality & Intimacy: Farcical timing, comedic blocking, and in some roles intimacy scenes (kissing / romantic chemistry) are required; also comedic violence or slapstick may appear.

As the play is set in 1923 England: RP / British accent is required.

Character Breakdown:
Sylvia
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s
Description: A ‚Äúlovely and rash romantic.‚Äù Sylvia is impulsive, passionate, and clings to romantic idealism. She‚Äôs the one who initiates the comedic uproar by deciding to reveal her affair which triggers the farcical unraveling of secrets.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should embody flirtatious charm, emotional volatility, and physical energy. Expect moments of passion/intimacy (kissing or romantic touch) and heightened comedic reactions or slapstick. 

Beau
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Beau is described as ‚Äúperhaps the best-looking man in Britain.‚Äù He‚Äôs charming, handsome, and somewhat complacent. A man comfortable with the status quo, even when his romantic life is scandalous. His affair with Sylvia is marked by both desire and hesitation.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should have presence, charm, and ease. Needs comfort with intimacy (romantic scenes) and comedic timing, especially with farcical elements. RP British accent.

Marjorie
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s (she is very pregnant in the play)
Description: Beau‚Äôs wife. ‚ÄúEight months pregnant, pragmatic‚Äù, grounded, and composed, even in the face of shocking revelations. Underneath, she has a sharp edge; she‚Äôs ‚Äúa tad spicy.‚Äù 
Physical / Performance Notes: You will be wearing an insanely pregnant-belly. Needs emotional range: from shock to self preservation to possible betrayal or strength. Comedic instincts + ability to react strongly to chaos.

Clarke
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Sylvia‚Äôs husband. A refined, ‚Äúdistinguished gent with a lover‚Äôs spirit.‚Äù He may appear respectable and stable, but underneath, his loyalties and feelings are complicated. Entangled in the web of affairs and deceptions.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs a balance of dignity and vulnerability. Believable as a gentleman, but also capable of comedic panic or confusion. Comfortable with farce pacing and quick reaction work. 

Dierdre
Gender: Female
Age: Early 20s to 30s (or thereabouts, though exact age is flexible)
Description: She‚Äôs described in the script as ‚Äúan awfully pretty, sometimes wise, nincompoop.‚Äù She‚Äôs na√Øve, sweet, perhaps a bit ditzy, but also occasionally offers piercing insight. She often reacts to the chaos with bewilderment and innocence, which amplifies the comedy.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs to deliver endearing innocence, comedic timing, and willingness to play ‚Äúditzy‚Äù with heart. Should be comfortable with exaggerated reactions, physical comedy and the heightened energy of farce. 

Richard
Gender: Male
Age: 30s to 50s
Description: A dark comedic twist in the farce. Richard is described as ‚Äúmurderous‚Äù but ‚Äúgentle,‚Äù meaning he occupies the role of destabilizing danger amidst the comedic chaos. His arrival triggers tension, threat, and unexpected comedy. A perfect blend of menace and absurdity.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should be able to handle heightened dramatic tension and farcical comedy. Perhaps a little brooding, but also capable of shambling comedy or over-the-top melodrama. Must be okay with comedic threat, possibly physical acting (gun or
threat).

Bring a headshot and resume and be ready to list ALL conflicts.

Performances: February 27 to March 22, 2026
Rehearsals Begin January 12 at Cabrillo Playhouse
All genders, body types, and ethnicities are encouraged to audition
There is a small stipend offered

items.text:
PURPLE DREAMS PRODUCTIONS are looking for several performers to join a few projects, primarily our brand new family-friendly play: 

THE PRINCESS & THE KNIGHT

a fantasy play written by Tobias Nicholls

Welcome to Twinklewood, a fantastical land where darkness and light have lived in harmony for decades‚Ä¶ until now.

Whilst the King is away on a royal tour, the Ruler of the Shadow Realm makes an unexpected appearance. Sir Milo is determined to keep his princess safe, but with her Kingdom thrown into chaos, Princess Nova - who has long dreamt of adventure - springs into action, taking them on a journey up to the highest mountain and down to the deepest, darkest cave.

Battles are fought and lessons learned on this funny and exciting quest.  

This brand new production is set to debut at The Seagull Theatre in Lowestoft on Saturday 4th April 2026

Two performances on the one day as a tester before we look at booking any others. 

The script is currently going through a rewrite, with the intention to have the cast help to develop the characters through the rehearsal process with the director. 

Adding to the fantastical nature of the story, the characters of Twinklewood will all feature likenesses to animals - realised through costume and make-up.  Aside from one, roles have not been assigned any particular animal, allowing the chosen actors can help build their character.

Payment: at this stage of development it‚Äôs best to consider this a profit share, although this could change to a flat fee - happy to have open and honest discussions with applicants. 

Rehearsals will take place at our studio in Hunstanton (PE36), and will be as flexible as possible to fit around other commitments.

If you are interested, or know someone that might be, please get in touch via a DM on here, or email purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk

## christmas time at The Three Crutches, 
##                       A traditional family-friendly pub

Ditzy, Sparkle and Tiny spread the Christmas cheer and Santa descended to The Three Crutches today. 

Located on the outskirts of Cobham woods on the scenic drive into Higham village, The Three Crutches provides a cosy respite from exploring the village and surrounding natural landscape. With local walks starting from their doorstep into the picturesque countryside, a welcome haven after a day exploring so sit back, relax and indulge in delicious food with your favourite drink in hand.

Merry Christmas everyone!

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Contestants should be outgoing, competitive and looking to have fun. We are producing a series of different shows that will be centered around Gen Z trivia, physical competitions and dating ‚Äì so there is a show for everyone!

In your submission, please let us know if you are single and want to be on a dating game show. We are open to all genders and sexual orientations.

Filming will take place January 2026 in Los Angeles, CA. All applicants must be at least 18 years old, live in the LA area and be US Citizens or permanent residents of the United States.

items.text:
STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING 

Shooting dates: 23rd-25th January

Location: Vancouver, North Vancouver

Volunteer, lunch and copy of film provided. 

**MARTY (20-25)**
* A young pianist struggling with anxiety and health issues. His passion for music is strong, but he is haunted by self-doubt and physical limitations. Emotionally vulnerable, he carries the weight of the past, yet despite the toll on his body and mind, he persists in pursuing his dreams.

**MARTY'S MOTHER (40s-50s)**
* A supportive, hard-working single mother. Cares deeply for her son and masks her worries about his skill with a calm, composed demeanor, despite the mental and physical toll it‚Äôs taking on her.

**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to an audition, January 7th. If unavailable, a self-tape will be accepted. 

**Submit to:** melodymovie2026@gmail.com

Marketing Macabre - a horror public relations company created to give independent filmmakers an affordable alternative. We focus on the importance of publicity to gain momentum and we work with some of the biggest genre websites in the world. Our mission is to get your project in front of your audience, the horror public - the most devoted fan base in all of entertainment.   

Our enhanced filmmaker services will supply you with everything needed on your cinematic journey from pre-production to post-production to distribution.  We have forged relationships out of trust and loyalty with partners that stretch from Hollywood studios to distribution companies.   In the evolution of horror, we have evolved from a marketing company to something more.  

A creation born out of necessity and a genesis into a one-stop-horror-shop that offers not only marketing, but opportunities in brand development, film funding, and distribution.  There are many complexities of making a feature film but our marketing militia will guide you on your journey and be your source to access the horror multiverse that is Marketing Macabre.

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races, ethnicities, and genders are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

Looking for a child aged 4-6 yrs old, dark haired, caucasian, who can ride a bike.

Fittings - 12/17

Shoot - 12/18 

Location - Atlanta, GA

To submit, please email hmcastingsubmissions@gmail.com

Subject line: BIKE KID
Body of email: Name, height, age of child, phone number, availability for shoot dates, minor work permit # for child (if you don't have one we will help you get this!), city/state you live in, professional headshot (if you have one), close up photo AND full body shot (taken recently)! (MUST BE RECENT AND REPRESENT YOUR CURRENT LOOK) (please no filters or crazy backgrounds for these), ***Bonus: If you have a video of them riding a bike or you can take one you get bonus points! :) ***

items.text:
Warmest Holiday Wishes from Our Creative Family to Yours!

As the season blankets Colorado and 2025 draws to a close, we at S.E.B. Casting, CSA want to take a moment to thank you for being part of our vibrant community of performers, directors, producers, advertisers, agents and creative visionaries. Your talent and passion continue to inspire us every day.

A Year of Breakthrough Performances
2025 has been extraordinary for the S.E.B. Casting community. From launching careers in award-winning productions to connecting diverse talent with innovative projects, we've watched with pride as performers have shined in everything from national commercials and viral ad campaigns to feature length films. Your commitment to authentic storytelling has helped productions across Colorado and beyond create more inclusive, powerful productions.

What's New at S.E.B.
We're thrilled to announce our studio expansion will be complete in January 2026! This means a more comofrtable audition space, improved casting facilities, and a dedicated area for talent and production. Plus, our Commitment to the Community will continue to grow, lifting individuals, groups. organizations and our whole state as a vibrant, positive, engaging, equitable hub for media arts and artists. 

Holiday Self-Care for Performers:
The holidays can be both magical and hectic for creative professionals. Here are our top tips to stay centered and ready for opportunities in the new year:

Schedule downtime: Block specific days for complete rest - no auditions, no rehearsals, no networking

Stay vocally healthy: Maintain your instrument with extra hydration and vocal rest during holiday gatherings

Update materials: Use the quiet period between December 20-January 5 to refresh headshots, reels, and resumes

Connect authentically: Attend industry gatherings not just for networking, but to genuinely celebrate the season with your creative community 

Here's to New Beginnings!
As we wrap up 2025, we're filled with gratitude for this remarkable community. The new year promises exciting productions, fresh opportunities, and continued growth for Colorado's vibrant media arts scene. Whether you're a seasoned professional or just beginning your journey, know that S.E.B. Casting, CSA is here to champion your unique voice and talent.

Grundkurs Filmschauspiel

Letzte Pl√§tze!

Beginn 16. Januar 2026 in Z√ºrich

Du willst:

‚Ä¢ Anhand von Filmbeispielen die Grundlagen des Kameraschauspiels kennen lernen.

‚Ä¢ Das Schauspielen vor der Kamera praktisch √ºben.

‚Ä¢ Die Dos des Sreenactings erlernen und die Don'ts erkennen.

‚Ä¢ Drei unterschiedliche Szenen mit professionellem Equipment drehen.

‚Ä¢ Die gedrehten Szenen analysieren und daraus lernen.

items.text:
S√∏ges: Skuespillere til kortfilm der skal optages henover sommeren 2026. Ul√∏nnet.

Da jeg g√•r med en lille vision om at bryde ud som director efter flere √•r som skuespiller i tv og film branchen. Har jeg endelig f√•et skrevet en af mine mange historier f√¶rdig, men da jeg gerne vil bryde lidt med normen s√• skiller dette projekt sig ud da det bogstaveligt er en silent montage film, sat til klassikeren "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi. 

Vores working title er indtil videre "The Mafia burial".
Filmen vil vare ca 20min og og vil indeholde en del slow motion og koreograferede blodige action shots. 

Kort synopsis: En respekteret Mafia boss har mistet sit et og alt, nemlig hans datter. Historien starter p√• en kirkeg√•rd hvor vi overv√¶rer hendes begravelse, med en hysterisk gr√¶dende mor, en masse s√∏rgende h√•ndlangere og mange kondolerende g√¶ster. Iblandt h√•ndlangerne st√•r vores hoved karakter. Da vi zoomer t√¶ttere p√• ham ser vi ham smide en lille t√•re, det der skiller ham ud er dog at det er mere end bare sorg vi kan se i ham, han er lige s√• knust som familien da han var datterens hemmelige elsker. Da vi zoomer mere ind p√• ham breaker vi over i hans tanker i form af en montage. Hvor vi ser ham eliminere og afh√∏re flere kriminelle i jagten p√• hans k√¶restes morder. Alt dette vil lede op til begravelsen. Der vil komme sm√• brud imellem hans voldelige handlinger hvor han sl√•r over til de sm√• gode k√¶rligheds stunder han havde med hende.

Der skildres imellem en tone af film som The Godfather og Drive. 

Da det hele basically er en silent movie s√• har vi ogs√• valgt at tage os ekstra god tid til at finde de helt rigtige skuespillere til projektet da der her udelukkende skal arbejdes med udtryk og mimik. 
Musikken som vil drive filmen vil v√¶re et mix af "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi samt nogle andre klassiske stykker. Det hele skydes rundt omkring i Midtjylland henover sommeren 2026, men laves til at ligne et m√∏rkt amerikansk drama. 

Dette er et komplet passion projekt s√• det hele er ul√∏nnet. Men der vil v√¶re forplejning og god stemning p√• alle set.

Action scener vil v√¶re koreograferet og vi arbejder efter et koncept hvor vi pr√∏ver at f√• s√• meget som muligt ud af s√• lidt som muligt mht til vinkler close ups and so on. 

Nogle af jer har nok set dette opslag i andre grupper og vi havde egentlig f√∏rst t√¶nkt os at begynde at caste skuespillere om en m√•neds tid. Men da rigtig mange af jer allerede har henvendt jer i h√•b om at udfylde en af de mange roller s√• kommer vores rolle liste her. 

Rolle...... (Alder)

Mafia Don, Marlon Brando vs John Turturro type(40-65)

Grieving Mafia mom, smuk sydlandsk look men skal kunne udtrykke ekstrem sorg og raseri (30-50)

Mafia Princess, sydlandsk look skal kunne udstr√•le positivt, hun er nemlig ikke som resten af hendes familie og er det eneste positive vores hovedrolle havde i sit liv (20-30)

The boyfriend, en Ryan gosling/Tom Hardy type(25-40) Hovedrollen, du skal v√¶re klar p√• at lave sm√• stunts og planlagte koreograferede fight sekvenser.

Bodyguard 1,2. Vores Mafia families personlige bodyguards kl√¶dt i sort sammen med vores hoved karakter. (30-50)

Bad guy 1,2,3,4,5 (20-40) I skal ogs√• v√¶re klar p√• at lave koreograferede fight sekvenser sammen med vores hovedrolle. 

Hitman, en fremh√¶vet bad guy der vil komme til at v√¶re m√•l for vores hovedrolles h√¶vntogt (30-50)

The other Don, en fremh√¶vet Mafia boss der sammen med sin egen familie vil v√¶re til stede under begravelsen og v√¶re fremh√¶vet som kondolerende (40-65).

Statister:

1) Der skal bruges statister under begravelsen, folk kl√¶dt i komplet sorte American style funeral outfits. 
Her skal vi bruge ca 10stk. Alder underordnet, der er dog plads til en ung statist ogs√• da vi godt kunne t√¶nke os at se et barn til stede under begravelsen, som spiller et evt familiemedlem.

2) Der skal bruges statister i baggrunden p√• nogle af vores flashbacks til vores karakterers k√¶rlighed stunder. Her skal vi bruge ca 8 personer med amerikansk hverdags look til sm√• optagelser i bla en park og evt Tivoli. 

3) Flygtende g√¶ster, n√•r vores hovedrolle konfronterer vores bad guys i en dinner, skal vi bruge ca 4 statister til at v√¶re g√¶ster i dinneren. 
Her skal man v√¶re klar p√• at f√• lidt fake blod p√• sig og evt smide lidt med tingene, da vi laver et slow motion shot der skal fange panikken i rummet. Alder og k√∏n er underordnet, men du skal kunne bev√¶ge dig hurtigt og forst√• en planlagt koreografi.

HUSK: At dette er en silent movie drevet af et klassisk soundtrack s√• derfor er det ekstra vigtigt at man kan arbejde med udtryk om mimik!

Det skal lige understreges at for at komme i betragtning til nogle af rollerne s√• SKAL ans√∏gningen sendes via email. Husk at skriv hvilken rolle i kunne v√¶re interesseret i og husk at sende opdaterede billeder for at kunne komme i betragtning. √ònsker man at medvirke som statist s√• husk at skriv om man det er gruppe 1,2 eller 3 man √∏nsker at medvirke i. Vi caster helt frem til 1.april og der vil ogs√• komme et et opslag p√• DASK hvor i kan ans√∏ge. Vi svarer kun p√• dem vi √∏nsker at bruge til projektet. S√• hvis det evt er noget for dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/4.2026

Pr√¶cis dato for optagelser er ikke fastlagt endnu, men holder alle vores udvalgte skuespillere og statister opdateret om forl√∏bet og projektet efterh√•nden som det skrider frem. 

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

Hitman, en fremh√¶vet bad guy der vil komme til at v√¶re m√•l for vores hovedrolles h√¶vntogt (30-50)

The other Don, en fremh√¶vet Mafia boss der sammen med sin egen familie vil v√¶re til stede under begravelsen og v√¶re fremh√¶vet som kondolerende (40-65).

Statister:

1) Der skal bruges statister under begravelsen, folk kl√¶dt i komplet sorte American style funeral outfits. 
Her skal vi bruge ca 10stk. Alder underordnet, der er dog plads til en ung statist ogs√• da vi godt kunne t√¶nke os at se et barn til stede under begravelsen, som spiller et evt familiemedlem.

2) Der skal bruges statister i baggrunden p√• nogle af vores flashbacks til vores karakterers k√¶rlighed stunder. Her skal vi bruge ca 8 personer med amerikansk hverdags look til sm√• optagelser i bla en park og evt Tivoli. 

3) Flygtende g√¶ster, n√•r vores hovedrolle konfronterer vores bad guys i en dinner, skal vi bruge ca 4 statister til at v√¶re g√¶ster i dinneren. 
Her skal man v√¶re klar p√• at f√• lidt fake blod p√• sig og evt smide lidt med tingene, da vi laver et slow motion shot der skal fange panikken i rummet. Alder og k√∏n er underordnet, men du skal kunne bev√¶ge dig hurtigt og forst√• en planlagt koreografi.

HUSK: At dette er en silent movie drevet af et klassisk soundtrack s√• derfor er det ekstra vigtigt at man kan arbejde med udtryk om mimik!

Det skal lige understreges at for at komme i betragtning til nogle af rollerne s√• SKAL ans√∏gningen sendes via email. Husk at skriv hvilken rolle i kunne v√¶re interesseret i og husk at sende opdaterede billeder for at kunne komme i betragtning. √ònsker man at medvirke som statist s√• husk at skriv om man det er gruppe 1,2 eller 3 man √∏nsker at medvirke i. Vi caster helt frem til 1.april og der vil ogs√• komme et et opslag p√• DASK hvor i kan ans√∏ge. Vi svarer kun p√• dem vi √∏nsker at bruge til projektet. S√• hvis det evt er noget for dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/4.2026

Pr√¶cis dato for optagelser er ikke fastlagt endnu, men holder alle vores udvalgte skuespillere og statister opdateret om forl√∏bet og projektet efterh√•nden som det skrider frem. 

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

items.text:
S√∏ges: Cinematographer/kameramand til kortfilm der skal optages henover sommeren 2026. Ul√∏nnet.

Da jeg g√•r med en lille vision om at bryde ud som director efter flere √•r som skuespiller i tv og film branchen. Har jeg endelig f√•et skrevet en af mine mange historier f√¶rdig, men da jeg gerne vil bryde lidt med normen s√• skiller dette projekt sig ud da det bogstaveligt er en silent montage film, sat til klassikeren "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi. 

Vores working title er indtil videre "The Mafia burial".
Filmen vil vare ca 20min og og vil indeholde en del slow motion og koreograferede blodige action shots. 

Kort synopsis: En respekteret Mafia boss har mistet sit et og alt, nemlig hans datter. Historien starter p√• en kirkeg√•rd hvor vi overv√¶rer hendes begravelse, med en hysterisk gr√¶dende mor, en masse s√∏rgende h√•ndlangere og mange kondolerende g√¶ster. Iblandt h√•ndlangerne st√•r vores hoved karakter. Da vi zoomer t√¶ttere p√• ham ser vi ham smide en lille t√•re, det der skiller ham ud er dog at det er mere en bare sorg vi kan se i ham, han er lige s√• knust som familien da han var datterens hemmelige elsker. Da vi zoomer mere ind p√• ham breaker vi over i hans tanker i form af en montage. Hvor vi ser ham eliminere og afh√∏re flere kriminelle i jagten p√• hans k√¶restes morder. Alt dette vil lede op til begravelsen. Der vil komme sm√• brud imellem hans voldelige handlinger hvor han sl√•r over til de sm√• gode k√¶rligheds stunder han havde med hende.

Der skildres imellem en tone af film som The Godfather og Drive. 

Da det hele basically er en silent movie s√• har vi ogs√• valgt at tage os ekstra god tid til at finde de helt rigtige skuespillere til projektet da der her udelukkende skal arbejdes med udtryk og mimik. 
Musikken som vil drive filmen vil v√¶re et mix af "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi samt nogle andre klassiske stykker. Det hele skydes rundt omkring i Midtjylland men laves til at ligne et m√∏rkt amerikansk drama. 

Dette er et komplet passion projekt s√• det hele er ul√∏nnet. Men der vil v√¶re forplejning og god stemning p√• alle set.

Action scener vil v√¶re koreograferet og vi arbejder efter et koncept hvor vi pr√∏ver at f√• s√• meget som muligt ud af s√• lidt som muligt mht til vinkler close ups and so on. 

Vi begynder f√∏rst at kigge efter skuespillere n√•r det rigtige crew er fundet. Men skulle man falde over det her og t√¶nke at det er lige noget for mig s√• er man mere end velkommen til at skrive til os. 
Men i f√∏rste omgang ledes der efter en kameramand der selv har det n√∏dvendige udstyr og som kan se vores vision. Gerne med henblik p√• et fremtidigt samarbejde til flere produktioner i fremtiden. S√• hvis det evt er dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/3.2026

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for optagelse og editing og har lyst til at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

items.text:
**CASTINGOPSLAG ‚Äì KORTFILM ‚ÄúALT I INTET‚Äù**

Vi s√∏ger **skuespillere i alderen 18‚Äì23 √•r** til hovedrollerne i vores kommende **ul√∏nnede kortfilm** *Alt I Intet*.
**Forplejning vil v√¶re inkluderet under optagelserne.**
Projektet har ambitioner om festivaldeltagelse og √∏nsker at skabe et v√¶rk, der kan n√• ud til et bredere publikum.

**Om projektet**

*‚ÄùAlt I Intet‚Äù* er et karakterdrevet drama, der unders√∏ger temaer som k√¶rlighed, sorg og identitet. Filmen bev√¶ger sig i gr√¶nselandet mellem virkelighed og erindring og skildrer en ung mands indre rejse efter et stort tab.

**Om os**

Vi er tre unge filmskabere med en f√¶lles passion for at skabe st√¶rke fort√¶llinger og ambiti√∏se filmiske v√¶rker med fokus p√• stemning, f√∏lelser og karakterudvikling.

 

**Roller**

**Oliver (mand, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Oliver er en ung, f√∏lsom og reflekterende mand, der er dybt knyttet til sine relationer. Udadtil fremst√•r han stille og n√¶sten anonym, som om han bev√¶ger sig gennem hverdagen p√• autopilot. Han lever prim√¶rt i minderne om sin afd√∏de k√¶reste, som fortsat p√•virker hans hverdag og selvforst√•else.

**Emma (kvinde, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Emma er en varm, n√¶rv√¶rende og livlig ung kvinde, der form√•r at se Oliver, n√•r han ikke selv kan. Hun repr√¶senterer b√•de k√¶rlighed, tryghed og det liv, Oliver har mistet.

 

**Logline**

Fortabt i minderne om Emma genoplever Oliver sit tab p√• gr√¶nsen mellem virkelighed og hallucinationer, indtil et m√∏de mellem liv og d√∏d giver ham et nyt blik p√• sig selv ‚Äì og p√• det liv, der stadig venter.

 

**Optagedatoer**

**L√∏rdag d. 7. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 8. marts**

**L√∏rdag d. 14. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 15. marts**

 

**Vigtig information**

Da filmen behandler temaer som k√¶rlighed og sorg, vil der indg√• semi-intime scener, herunder kram, h√•ndholdning og t√¶t fysisk kontakt.

For den kvindelige rolle forekommer der enkelte scener i badet√∏j. Disse scener har ingen seksuel karakter og vil blive behandlet med respekt og tydelig kommunikation.

 

**Ans√∏gning**

Vi ser gerne, at interesserede sender f√∏lgende:

**Selftape**

**Portr√¶tbillede**

**Alder og h√∏jde**

Ans√∏gning og eventuelle sp√∏rgsm√•l kan sendes via:
**E-mail:** magn715c@gmail.com
**Messenger: **Undertegnet

Vi ser frem til at h√∏re fra jer.

 

**Venlig hilsen**
**Magnus Petersen**
Producer ‚Äì ‚Äù*Alt I Intet‚Äù*
p√• vegne af filmens crew

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

**TITLE: ***THE LAST HIKE*
**FORMAT: **Short Film
**LOCATION: **North and West Yorkshire (on-location shoot) - exact locations TBC.
**DATES: **April (3 shoot dates)
**Expenses, travel and hot food covered, along with Associate Producer credit on film, and a handcrafted ceramic keepsake.**

Deadline: 12th Jan 2026

**SYNOPSIS:**
*The Last Hike follows Daniel, a reserved man who reluctantly returns to his working-class roots in Yorkshire to scatter a loved one's ashes.*

*Joined by his mother, their hike through the Yorkshire Dales becomes more than just a physical journey ‚Äî it‚Äôs a path through shared memories, complicated family history and unspoken emotions.*

*Against the rugged, fading landscape of their hometown, Daniel and his mother confront the past, navigating the challenges of grief, mental health and reconciliation.*

*See our successful fundraising campaign here to learn more about the team and the project!*
[[https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/cameronstott/the-last-hike-short-film#/section/project-story](https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/cameronstott/the-last-hike-short-film#/section/project-story)](https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/cameronstott/the-last-hike-short-film#/section/project-story)* *

**ROLES:**
* **DANIEL (38-45, Male)**

Emotionally reserved, sharp-edged, physically capable for hiking scenes. Must deliver restrained but intense emotional beats.

* **MUM (58-65, Female)**
Warm and expressive, with the ability to shift between lightness and emotional volatility. Strong dramatic instincts essential.

* **YOUNG DANIEL (4-7, Male) - Will also need a caregiver with them.**
Gentle, expressive child performer. Short scenes requiring natural reactions and simple physical actions.

**ACCENT:**

Yorkshire accents!

**TO APPLY:**
Please send: Full name, headshots, showreel links, filming availability for around April and the general area you‚Äôre based in to *thelasthikefilm@gmail.com*

with the subject line ‚ÄúTHE LAST HIKE ‚Äì ROLE NAME‚Äù.

30 min Short Film / Proof-of-concept pilot Episode (Graduation Project)

We are casting PAZUZU, a supernatural entity in a dark, poetic fantasy-horror pilot.

Age: Open (25s‚Äì40s)

Gender: Open

Location: Berlin

Production: Independent / Graduation Project

Compensation: Unpaid, meals + credits + content for showreel.

Shooting days: January 19 - 24 

Pazuzu will require 2 shooting days. 

Pazuzu is not a traditional demon.

He is intelligent, unstable, and addicted to souls, not out of cruelty, but desperation. He is caught

between cosmic power and emotional decay.

This role requires:

‚óè Strong presence and restraint

‚óè Comfort with psychological intensity

‚óè Ability to shift between charm, menace, humor, and vulnerability

‚óè Voice and stillness are as important as physicality

If interested:

Please email for self-tape instructions to

celia.t@catalyst-students.com

items.text:
What Kills Self-Tapes So Fast?

Why do casting directors stop watching self-tapes so quickly? It‚Äôs rarely about talent. More often, it‚Äôs about preparation.

In this video, we break down how actors can use modern audition AI and acting practice apps to prepare smarter, not harder. Instead of memorizing lines blindly, actors can rehearse with an AI acting assistant that helps define objectives, obstacles, and emotional flow.
Using an actor teleprompter app, self-tape reader app, or acting lines rehearsal tool, actors can focus on performance instead of recall. Advanced tools like a scene analysis tool for actors and acting script breakdown tool help performers understand the story they‚Äôre telling before stepping on camera.

With a full audition preparation app, actors gain access to self-tape coaching tools, AI reader for self-tapes, and a self-tape performance analyzer that turns guesswork into clarity.

Whether you‚Äôre preparing a cold read, rehearsing remotely, or looking for professional self-tape tools, this new generation of actor training tools makes it possible to deliver confident, clear performances from anywhere.

If you want better callbacks without more stress, the solution isn‚Äôt more takes ‚Äî it‚Äôs better preparation.

üëâ Go to myauditionai.com and get 7 days free
Stop losing roles before your talent even shows up.
